File: Emergency paramedics wearing a full COVID-19 coronavirus personal protective equipment (PPE) transfer an empty gurney to an ambulance at the Greenacres Hospital in Port Elizabeth. Marco Longari / AFP JOHANNESBURG - The surge in COVID-19 numbers continues. In the last 24 hours, 21,606 new infections have been added. It's the fourth day in a row that more than 20,000 cases have been confirmed. READ: COVID-19 infections expected to rise in Gauteng This takes the total number of cases to over 1,2 million. Three-hundred and ninety-nine new deaths have been reported, taking the death toll to 32,824. Over 900,000 people have already recovered from the virus. More than 7- million tests have been conducted, over 77,000 of those since the last report.